<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,496,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1288,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Notes:—</emphasis>
An additional specimen from nearby 
<collectingRegion box="[704,851,1288,1314]" country="Thailand" name="Tak" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Tak Province</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[884,984,1288,1314]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Thailand</collectingCountry>
was unfortunately lost, but the flower was photographed (
<figureCitation box="[307,397,1324,1350]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1645,1667]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,815,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-289@4.[170,1416,814,1620]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of new Trivalvaria species. A. Flower of Trivalvaria stenopetala, Phangnga Province, Thailand. B. Flower of Trivalvaria ochroleuca, Tak Province, Thailand. C. Flower of Trivalvaria recurva, Kanchanaburi Province, Thailand. D. Fruit of Trivalvaria stenopetala, Phangnga Province, Thailand. E. Fruit of probable Trivalvaria ochroleuca from Prachuap Khiri Khan Province, Thailand. F. Fruit of Trivalvaria recurva from Kanchanaburi Province, Thailand.A and D by Simon Gardner from Gardner et al. ST 1944, B by Tanawat Chaowasku, C and F by Piya Chalermglin, E by Thammanoon Temchai." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). A DNA sequence was obtained for phylogenetic analysis (Chaowasku, unpubl.). Similarly, the fruit (
<figureCitation box="[244,330,1360,1386]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1645,1667]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,815,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-289@4.[170,1416,814,1620]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of new Trivalvaria species. A. Flower of Trivalvaria stenopetala, Phangnga Province, Thailand. B. Flower of Trivalvaria ochroleuca, Tak Province, Thailand. C. Flower of Trivalvaria recurva, Kanchanaburi Province, Thailand. D. Fruit of Trivalvaria stenopetala, Phangnga Province, Thailand. E. Fruit of probable Trivalvaria ochroleuca from Prachuap Khiri Khan Province, Thailand. F. Fruit of Trivalvaria recurva from Kanchanaburi Province, Thailand.A and D by Simon Gardner from Gardner et al. ST 1944, B by Tanawat Chaowasku, C and F by Piya Chalermglin, E by Thammanoon Temchai." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) of a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miquel" authorityYear="1865" baseAuthorityName="Miquel" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[401,527,1360,1386]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[401,527,1360,1386]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Trivalvaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plant photographed in 
<collectingRegion box="[794,1144,1360,1386]" country="Thailand" name="Prachuap Khiri Khan" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Prachuap Khiri Khan Province</collectingRegion>
is probably this species. A specimen collected by Gallatly from a slightly higher elevation in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[986,1095,1397,1423]" name="Myanmar" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
(Molyet, 
<quantity box="[1206,1296,1396,1423]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="ft" value="5000.0">5000 ft.</quantity>
, 
<date box="[1308,1447,1396,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" value="1877-01-19">19 Jan 1877</date>
, K), cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="King, G." box="[276,459,1432,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" pagination="1 - 130" refId="ref5279" refString="King, G. (1892) Materials for a flora of the Malay Peninsula, no. 4. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, Part 2, Natural History 61: 1 - 130." type="journal article" year="1892">King (1892: 27)</bibRefCitation>
, under 
<taxonomicName authority="King" authorityName="King" authorityYear="1892" baseAuthorityName="Hook.f. &amp; Thomson" box="[541,784,1432,1458]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Ellipeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis box="[541,718,1432,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Ellipeia costata</emphasis>
King
</taxonomicName>
, may also represent this species.
</paragraph>
